## Confluence Publishing Workflow

### Pre-Publishing Checklist
- [ ] Document reviewed and proofread
- [ ] All links verified and working
- [ ] Images/screenshots included and optimized
- [ ] Tags/labels added
- [ ] Page permissions set correctly
- [ ] Related pages linked
- [ ] Table of contents added (for long documents)

### Confluence Page Structure
1. **Page Title**: Clear, descriptive, searchable
2. **Labels**: Add relevant labels (e.g., `prd`, `status-report`, `product`, `feature`)
3. **Space**: Publish to appropriate space (e.g., Product, Engineering, Company)
4. **Parent Page**: Link to parent page if part of a hierarchy
5. **Table of Contents**: Use Confluence macro for documents > 3 sections

### Publishing Workflow Steps
1. **Draft Creation**
   - Create page in Confluence
   - Use appropriate template (if available)
   - Add content following structure guidelines

2. **Review Process**
   - Share draft link with reviewers
   - Collect feedback
   - Make revisions
   - Get approval (if required)

3. **Final Publishing**
   - Set page permissions (view/edit)
   - Add to relevant space navigation (if applicable)
   - Add watchers/notifications
   - Publish page

4. **Post-Publishing**
   - Share link with stakeholders
   - Add to index/landing pages
   - Update related pages with links
   - Archive old versions (if updating existing page)

### Confluence Page Types & Templates

**PRD Pages**
- Space: Product/Product Requirements
- Template: PRD Template
- Labels: `prd`, `requirements`, `[feature-name]`
- Parent: Product Requirements Index

**Status Reports**
- Space: Product/Status Reports
- Template: Status Report Template
- Labels: `status-report`, `weekly-update`, `[team-name]`
- Parent: Status Reports Archive
- Create monthly/quarterly summary pages

**Meeting Notes**
- Space: Product/Meetings
- Template: Meeting Notes Template
- Labels: `meeting-notes`, `[meeting-type]`, `[date]`
- Include: Attendees, Agenda, Decisions, Action Items

**Feature Documentation**
- Space: Product/Features
- Template: Feature Documentation Template
- Labels: `feature-doc`, `[feature-name]`
- Link to: PRD, Design files, Jira epic

### Confluence Best Practices
- Use consistent formatting (headers, lists, tables)
- Include screenshots/mockups with alt text
- Add "Last Updated" date at top of page
- Use page properties macro for metadata
- Create child pages for detailed sections
- Link related pages in "Related Pages" section
- Use expand macros for long content
- Add comments for discussions (don't edit main content)

### Version Control
- Use Confluence version history for major changes
- Add version notes explaining changes
- Archive superseded pages to Archive space
- Keep current version easily accessible

